---
description: Add GPL licence header to all new source files in the /calycopis project
alwaysApply: true
---

When you create a new source file in the `/calycopis` project, add the following GPL licence header at the very top of the file, before any code.

Adapt the comment syntax to match the file type as shown below.

### Python files (`.py`), YAML files (`.yaml`, `.yml`), and other `#`-commented files:

```
#
# <meta:header>
#   <meta:licence>
#     Copyright (c) 2026, Manchester (http://www.manchester.ac.uk/)
#
#     This information is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
#     it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
#     the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or
#     (at your option) any later version.
#
#     This information is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
#     but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
#     MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the
#     GNU General Public License for more details.
#
#     You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
#     along with this software. If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
#   </meta:licence>
# </meta:header>
#
# AIMetrics: []
#
```

### Java files (`.java`):

```
/*
 * <meta:header>
 *   <meta:licence>
 *     Copyright (c) 2026, Manchester (http://www.manchester.ac.uk/)
 *
 *     This information is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
 *     it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
 *     the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or
 *     (at your option) any later version.
 *
 *     This information is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
 *     but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
 *     MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the
 *     GNU General Public License for more details.
 *
 *     You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
 *     along with this software. If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
 *   </meta:licence>
 * </meta:header>
 *
 * AIMetrics: []
 *
 */
```

### XML files (`.xml`):

```
<!--
 - <meta:header>
 -   <meta:licence>
 -     Copyright (c) 2026, Manchester (http://www.manchester.ac.uk/)
 -
 -     This information is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
 -     it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
 -     the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or
 -     (at your option) any later version.
 -
 -     This information is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
 -     but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
 -     MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the
 -     GNU General Public License for more details.
 -
 -     You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
 -     along with this software. If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
 -   </meta:licence>
 - </meta:header>
 -
 - AIMetrics: []
 -
 -->
```

Rules:
- The copyright year must be the current year at the time the file is created.
- The `AIMetrics` block starts as `[]` and will be populated by the ai-metrics rule.
- The header must be the very first content in the file (before any `package`, `import`, `"""`, or `<?xml` declarations).
- Do not add a licence header if the file already has a `<meta:licence>` block.
